LXC â€“ 
LinuX Containers (LXC) is an OS level virtualization method for running multiple isolated Linux systems (containers) on a single control host(LXC host)

Docker - 
A container system making use of LXC containers

LXD - 
You can run LXD on Ubuntu and spin up instances of RHEL, CentOS, SUSE, Debian, Ubuntu and just about any other linux too instantly.

Docker VS LXD
Docker specialized in deploying containers
LXD specialized in deploying Linux VM

Minor Technical note:
installing LXD includes a command line program coincidentally named lxc.
